aily%20by%2020%25.%20Each%20said%20their%20location%20is%20experiencing%20normal%20turnover%20but%20not%20receiving%20new%20hires%20to%20replace%20those%20who%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20federal%20hiring%20freeze%20is%20partly%20to%20blame.%20MEPCOM%20has%20an%20exemption%20to%20hire%20essential%20workers%2C%20but%20the%20additional%20approvals%20needed%20for%20those%20hires%20have%20created%20a%20bureaucratic%20quagmire.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20approval%20process%20has%20delayed%20hires%20by%20as%20much%20as%20six%20months%2C%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Department%20of%20Defense%20is%20reorganizing%20and%20optimizing%20its%20workforce%20to%20best%20support%20its%20top%20priorities%20and%20meet%20its%20mission%2C%20now%20and%20in%20the%20future%20as%20part%20of%20its%20workforce%20optimization%20initiatives%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20command%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%20that%20also%20referenced%20MEPCOM's%20exemption%20from%20the%20hiring%20freeze%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efor%20essential%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20applicants%20a%20facility%20can%20process%20fluctuates%20periodically%2C%20the%20statement%20said%2C%20which%20was%20supported%20by%20sources%20who%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20current%20staffing%20attrition%20rate%20continues%2C%20more%20locations%20will%20be%20forced%20to%20lower%20the%20number%20of%20applicants%20they%20can%20screen%20daily%2C%20a%20senior%20official%20said.%20Over%20the%20longer%20term%2C%20this%20could%20impact%20the%20rate%20of%20military%20recruitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20services%20have%20recently%20started%20to%20turn%20the%20corner%20on%20a%20yearslong%20recruiting%20crisis.%20Until%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Army%20and%20Navy%2C%20and%20to%20a%20lesser%20extent%2C%20the%20Air%20Force%2C%20have%20fallen%20thousands%20of%20recruits%20short%20for%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20The%20Pentagon%20has%20touted%20the%20recent%20higher%20recruiting%20numbers%20as%20evidence%20of%20a%20patriotic%20%26quot%3BTrump%20Bump%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20evidence%20suggests%20it's%20a%20mix%20of%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226012%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Navy%20recruits%20take%20the%20naturalization%20oath%20of%20allegiance%20during%20a%20naturalization%20ceremony%20at%20Navy%20Recruit%20Training%20Command%20at%20Great%20Lakes%2C%20Illinois%20on%20Mar.%2027%2C%202025.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689397b1f748d8c055f700a6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224008%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENavy%20recruits%20take%20the%20naturalization%20oath%20of%20allegiance%20during%20a%20naturalization%20ceremony%20at%20Navy%20Recruit%20Training%20Command%20at%20Great%20Lakes%2C%20Illinois%20on%20Mar.%2027%2C%202025.%3Cp%3EMass%20Communication%20Specialist%201st%20Class%20Christopher%20M.%20O'Grady%2FUS%20Navy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ceb465a-f75c-4e2e-a7c6-5b6fdffe26e9%5C%22%3E'Do%20it%20with%20less%20resources'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESources%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20major%20metropolitan%20MEPCOM%20locations%20have%20a%20notoriously%20hard%20time%20retaining%20staff%2C%20including%20administrators%20who%20oversee%20applicant%20histories%20and%20processing%2C%20IT%20workers%2C%20and%20medical%20technicians.%20High%20costs%20of%20living%20and%20low%20government%20salaries%20lead%20to%20high%20turnover%2C%20forcing%20MEPCOM%20to%20rely%20on%20a%20steady%20stream%20of%20new%20hires%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20issues%20have%20been%20exacerbated%2C%20in%20part%2C%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20deferred%20resignation%20program%20%E2%80%94%20essentially%20a%20buyout%20that%20has%20also%20been%20offered%20to%20civilian%20workers.%20To%20date%2C%2015%2C000%20civilian%20workers%20within%20the%20Army%20have%20taken%20the%20buyout%2C%20an%20Army%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%20Though%20MEPCOM%20supports%20all%20services%2C%20it%20is%20managed%20by%20the%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wobbly%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Estaffing%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20MEPCOM's%20work%20volume%20has%20ballooned%2C%20rising%20annually%20by%20tens%20of%20thousands.%20In%202022%2C%20they%20processed%20215%2C000%20medical%20exams%20alone%2C%20another%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esenior%20official%20said.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20it%20was%20312%2C000.%20The%20command%20has%20already%20exceeded%20that%20number%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%2065%20MEPCOM%20locations%2C%20fewer%20than%2020%20process%20over%20half%20of%20all%20the%20nation's%20applicants%2C%20a%20senior%20official%20said.%20Some%20of%20those%20are%20locations%20hardest%20hit%20by%20hiring%20challenges%2C%20he%20added%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Espeaking%20from%20direct%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20pressure%20on%20one%20side%20to%20increase%20efficiency%20processing%20applicants%20at%20the%20MEPS%2C%20which%20requires%20resources%20to%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20official%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20local%20MEPCOM%20facilities%20known%20as%20Military%20Entrance%20Processing%20Stations%2C%20or%20MEPS.%20%26quot%3BKeep%20the%20numbers%20flowing%2C%20keep%20things%20efficient%20in%20terms%20of%20when%20the%20applicants%20are%20being%20processed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BBut%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20do%20it%20with%20less%20resources.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-command-that-okays-military-recruits-approaching-crisis-point-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754902802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6893b87f3d5881a51c1ebdd5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-comman