ntries%2C%20and%20a%20series%20of%20product-specific%20duties%2C%20including%20on%20automobiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20consumers%20have%20absorbed%20just%2022%25%20of%20the%20tariff%20costs%20associated%20with%20this%20year's%20increases%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20Goldman%20Sachs%20report%20published%20Sunday.%20But%20by%20October%2C%20that%20share%20could%20rise%20to%2067%25%2C%20if%20pricing%20patterns%20continue%20to%20follow%20those%20observed%20earlier%20in%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20reached%20that%20conclusion%20by%20analyzing%20import%20and%20consumer%20price%20data%20through%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDescriptive%20evidence%20shows%20that%20goods%20categories%20heavily%20exposed%20to%20imports%20have%20indeed%20experienced%20sizable%20price%20increases%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20this%20year%2C%20relative%20to%20their%20prior%20trends%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecifically%2C%20prices%20of%20household%20appliances%20and%20information%20processing%20equipment%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20computers%20and%20electronics%20%E2%80%94%20have%20increased%20by%207.5%20percentage%20points%20more%20than%20what%20they%20would've%20cost%20without%20the%20tariffs%2C%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20especially%20striking%20is%20who's%20been%20absorbing%20tariff%20costs%20so%20far.%20US%20businesses%20have%20born%20the%20brunt%2C%20covering%20about%2064%25%20of%20costs%20through%20midyear%2C%20Goldman%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20foreign%20exporters%20have%20cut%20prices%20to%20stay%20competitive%2C%20absorbing%20around%2014%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20expected%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Goldman%2C%20tariffs%20have%20already%20contributed%20about%200.20%20percentage%20points%20to%20core%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-supercore-inflation-fed-new-term-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPersonal%20Consumption%20Expenditures%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20preferred%20inflation%20measure.%20They%20expect%20an%20additional%200.16%25%20increase%20in%20July%2C%20and%20another%200.5%25%20from%20August%20through%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-raising-prices-increases-trump-tariffs-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emajor%20companies%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0including%20Adidas%20and%20Walmart%2C%20have%20said%20that%20they%20will%20be%20hiking%20prices%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20consumers%20may%20face%20higher%20prices%20on%20everything%20from%20electronics%20to%20cars%20heading%20into%20the%20holiday%20shopping%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20expects%20core%20PCE%20inflation%20at%203.2%25%20year%20over%20year%20by%20December%20%E2%80%94%20well%20above%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target.%20Without%20tariffs%2C%20Goldman%20says%2C%20the%20underlying%20inflation%20trend%20would%20be%20closer%20to%202.4%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETreasury%20data%20shows%20that%20the%20federal%20government%20has%20collected%20over%20%24100%20billion%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftariffs-prices-import-export-deutsche-bank-analysts-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecustoms%20duties%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20far%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sign%20that%20%26quot%3Bsomeone%20is%20paying%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20tariffs%2C%20wrote%20Deutsche%20Bank%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-trade-tariffs-consumers-import-costs-inflation-goldman-sachs-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754902005000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68995ceba17a8c5b40529e8a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-trade-tariffs-consumers-import-costs-inflation-goldman-sachs-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%