survey%20from%20the%20SHRM%20found.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foffice-crushes-jim-pam-metoo-pandemic-remote-work-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECrushes%20tend%20to%20make%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20put%20their%20best%20foot%20forward%20and%20can%20boost%20morale%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20can%20also%20lead%20to%20distractions%20and%20drama%20if%20feelings%20are%20unrequited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20loud%20chorus%20of%20workers%20want%20to%20stay%20home%20and%20work%20in%20sweatpants%20until%20they%20retire%2C%20a%20quieter%20contingent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-wants-to-go-in-office-bosses-dont-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewants%20to%20work%20in-person%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20learn%20the%20ropes%20from%20superiors%2C%20and%20because%20they%20have%20corporate%20FOMO.%20%26quot%3BIt%20just%20depends%20on%20the%20stage%20of%20life%20that%20you're%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Julia%20Toothacre%2C%20a%20career%20consultant.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20why%20we're%20seeing%20so%20many%20more%20of%20the%20younger%20generation%20be%20OK%20going%20back%20into%20office%20or%20wanting%20that%20experience%20so%20that%20they%20can%20expand%20their%20social%20circle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20haven't%20been%20in%20the%20workplace%20for%20long%2C%20but%20Gen%20Z%20is%20eagerly%20looking%20for%20love%2C%20or%20at%20least%20a%20hookup.%20They're%20most%20likely%20to%20have%20had%20an%20intimate%20relationship%20with%20a%20coworker%3A%2045%25%2C%20compared%20to%2042%25%20of%20Millennials%2C%2035%25%20of%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20and%2021%25%20of%20Boomers%2C%20according%20to%20a%202024%20survey%20of%201%2C000%20US%20workers%20from%20Resume%20Genius%20conducted%20with%20Pollfish.%20Gen%20Zers%20were%20also%20the%20most%20likely%20to%20report%20having%20a%20relationship%20with%20their%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20from%20SHRM%20also%20shows%20the%20taboo%20is%20waning%20for%20younger%20workers.%20Nearly%2060%25%20of%20Millennials%20and%2049%25%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-most-rejected-generation-college-careers-jobs-dating-ghosting-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%20say%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E%20romance%20has%20become%20more%20accepted%2C%20compared%20to%20just%2025%25%20of%20Baby%20Boomers.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20suggesting%20that%20there%20might%20be%20some%20shifts%20happening%20in%20terms%20of%20acceptance%20and%20attitudes%20towards%20workplace%20romance%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ragan%20Decker%2C%20a%20manager%20of%20commercial%20research%20at%20SHRM.%20%26quot%3BWe%20shouldn't%20be%20afraid%20of%20workplace%20romances%2C%20as%20long%20as%20we're%20prepared%20with%20the%20right%20policies%20and%20communication%20in%20place%20to%20proactively%20manage%20them.%26quot%3B%20SHRM's%20survey%20also%20asked%20more%20than%202%2C000%20HR%20professionals%20about%20their%20policies%20regarding%20office%20romances.%20Just%205%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20had%20strict%20policies%20that%20discouraged%20or%20banned%20them%2C%20while%20nearly%2030%25%20said%20they%20did%20not%20have%20any%20policies%20or%20were%20developing%20some.%20Another%20third%20said%20they%20handle%20them%20on%20a%20case-by-case%20basis%2C%20and%20a%20third%20said%20they%20have%20policies%20that%20permit%20romances%20with%20clear%20boundaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20workplace%20butterflies%20may%20be%20driven%20more%20by%20what%20social%20psychologists%20call%20the%20'proximity%20principle'%20than%20by%20compatibility.%20Seeing%20people%20frequently%20can%20increase%20our%20attraction%20to%20them%2C%20whether%20platonic%20or%20romantic.%20Think%20of%20this%20as%20the%20slow%20burn%20%E2%80%94%20one%20day%2C%20your%20coworker%20is%20just%20someone%20in%20wrinkled%20khakis%20at%20the%20water%20cooler%2C%20but%20over%20time%2C%20you%20notice%20and%20appreciate%20their%20quirks%20or%20hidden%20strengths.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcerca-dating-app-matches-mutual-connections-friends-pitch-deck-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDating%20apps%20operate%20entirely%20differently%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20banking%20on%20initial%20attraction%20between%20people%20who%20may%20have%20few%20to%20no%20connections%20or%20common%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proximity%20principle%20is%20one%20Cassie%20Richardson%2C%20a%2032-year-old%20working%20in%20retail%20in%20Tennessee%2C%20says%20she%20knows%20well.%20Richardson%20tells%20me%20she's%20had%20a%20handful%20of%20workplace%20crushes%20since%20starting%20her%20career%2C%20and%20just%20one%20that%20turned%20into%20a%20situationship.%20It%20didn't%20end%20well.%20As%20she%20found%20herself%20falling%20deeper%20into%20her%20feelings%20for%20her%20coworker%2C%20she%20realized%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20not%20even%20approach%20this%20person%20if%20I%20were%20outside%20of%20this%20store%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Now%2C%20Richardson%20says%2C%20she%20wouldn't%20mix%20work%20and%20love%20again%2C%20though%20she%20understands%20the%20appeal%20of%20falling%20for%20someone%20working%20alongside%20you%20in%20a%20world%20where%20it's%20hard%20to%20connect%20with%20new%20people.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20to%20work%20really%20hard%20to%20go%20out%20and%20do%20things%20and%20meet%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Richardson%20says.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20working%20eight%20hours%20a%20day%20for%2040%20hours%20a%20week%2C%20that%20can%20be%20exhausting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESparks%20can%20fly%20even%20when%20workers%20are%20remote.%20A%202025%20survey%20from%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20writing%20site%20Zety%20found%2062%25%20of%20people%20had%20sent%20a%20flirty%20message%20over%20platforms%20like%20Slack%2C%20Microsoft%20Teams%2C%20or%20email.%20When%20Isabel%20Amat%20started%20her%20first%20software%20developer%20job%20in%202021%2C%20she%20met%20her%20coworkers%20first%20over%20Zoom.%20She%20thought%20one%20was%20cute%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20until%20she%20started%20going%20to%20the%20office%20that%20fall%20that%20she%20realized%20how%20much%20she%20liked%20her%20fellow%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-ladder-software-engineers-collapsing-ai-google-meta-coding-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoftware%20engineer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20two%20went%20out%20for%20a%20solo%20happy%20hour%20after%20their%20coworkers%20bailed%20and%20stayed%20for%20five%20hours.%20Amat%20tells%20me%20the%20restaurant%20manager%20brought%20them%20a%20round%20on%20the%20house%2C%20comping%20the%20drinks%20because%20the%20staff%20thought%20they%20were%20a%20cute%20couple.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20like%2C%20'We're%20coworkers%2C'%20and%20the%20guy%20scoffed%20in%20our%20faces.%20He%20was%20like%2C%20'not%20for%20long%2C'%26quot%3B%20Amat%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20snide%20remark%20opened%20the%20door%20for%20the%20pair%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20chemistry%20everyone%20else%20could%20see%20that%20they%20had%20been%20denying.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20so%20relieved.%26quot%3B%20Days%20later%2C%20they%20went%20on%20a%20real%20date%2C%20and%20nearly%20four%20years%20later%2C%20they're%20still%20together%2C%20although%20Amat%20has%20taken%20a%20different%20job.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20that%20would%20have%20happened%20if%20we%20weren't%20in%20person%20every%20day%2C%20talking%20every%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20maybe%20would%20have%20had%20a%20crush%2C%20and%20then%20it%20probably%20would%20have%20eventually%20fizzled%20out%20because%20we're%20not%20seeing%20each%20other.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20every%20workplace%20romance%20that%20lasts%2C%20there%20are%20others%20that%20devolve%20into%20awkwardness%2C%20broken%20hearts%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-hr-workers-miserable-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHR%20issues%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Half%20of%20workers%20seem%20to%20think%20it's%20worth%20the%20risk.%20With%20more%20