sinsider.com%2Famazon-employees-criticize-ceo-jassys-ai-driven-job-cutting-plan-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndy%20Jassy%20had%20a%20blunt%20message%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20his%20350%2C000%20corporate%20employees%3A%20There%20were%20going%20to%20be%20fewer%20of%20them%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Befficiency%20gains%26quot%3B%20he%20expected%20from%20AI.%20The%20proclamation%20generated%20big%20headlines%20and%20an%20uproar%20from%20staff.%20But%20it%20struck%20me%20as%20merely%20honest.%20He%20was%20acknowledging%20something%20that%20pretty%20much%20every%20CEO%20who%20sits%20atop%20a%20large%20white-collar%20workforce%20is%20quietly%20hoping%20to%20achieve%20sooner%20or%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20Jassy%20hasn't%20been%20the%20only%20executive%20to%20hint%20at%20a%20future%20of%20lower%20headcount.%20The%20head%20of%20JPMorgan's%20consumer%20and%20community%20business%20predicted%20in%20May%20that%20AI%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-investor-day-resist-hiring-headcount-ai-efficiencies-jamie-dimon-2025-5%3Futm_source%3Dcopy-link%26utm_medium%3Dreferral%26utm_content%3Dtopbar%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereduce%20the%20number%20of%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20operations%20division%20by%2010%25.%20That%20same%20month%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Klarna%20said%20that%20the%20company's%20investments%20in%20AI%20has%20already%20driven%20the%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2025%2F05%2F14%2Fklarna-ceo-says-ai-helped-company-shrink-workforce-by-40percent.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheadcount%20to%20shrink%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%2040%25.%20And%20the%20CEO%20of%20Ford%20%E2%80%94%20a%20company%20that%20employs%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20white-collar%20professionals%20%E2%80%94%20declared%20that%20AI%20will%20wipe%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fford-ceo-jim-farley-ai-eliminate-half-white-collar-jobs-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bliterally%20half%26quot%3B%20of%20all%20white-collar%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Kian%20Katanforoosh%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20software%20startup%20Workera%2C%20tells%20me%20that%20he%20never%20wants%20to%20have%20much%20more%20than%20the%2080%20or%20so%20employees%20he%20has%20today%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20successful%20his%20business%20ends%20up%20becoming.%20%26quot%3BI%20truly%20believe%20we%20can%20go%20super%20super%20far%20without%20growing%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20an%20engineer.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20have%20to%20manage%20so%20many%20people%20if%20I%20don't%20need%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20like%20CEOs%20ever%20%3Cem%3Eenjoyed%3C%2Fem%3E%20shelling%20out%20for%20the%20salaries%20or%20navigating%20the%20personnel%20headaches%20that%20come%20with%20the%20sprawling%20bureaucracies%20they%20employ.%20But%20for%20more%20than%20a%20century%2C%20armies%20of%20office%20workers%20were%20a%20necessary%20cost%20of%20doing%20business.%20To%20grow%20from%20tiny%20upstarts%20into%20titans%20of%20industry%2C%20companies%20needed%20an%20ever-multiplying%20number%20of%20HR%20reps%2C%20accountants%2C%20marketers%2C%20engineers%2C%20analysts%2C%20and%20project%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20months%2C%20that%20100-year-trend%20is%20starting%20to%20come%20undone.%20Everywhere%20you%20look%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-hiring-white-collar-recession-jobs-tech-new-data-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20appears%20to%20be%20helping%20leaner%20teams%3C%2Fa%3E%20take%20on%20work%20that%20used%20to%20require%20more%20people.%20And%20executives%20are%20talking%20about%20their%20large%20workforces%20%E2%80%94%20once%20their%20greatest%20competitive%20advantage%20%E2%80%94%20as%20if%20they're%20an%20unfortunate%20holdover%20from%20a%20bygone%2C%20bloated%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20today's%20corporate%20giants%20shrink%20their%20ranks%2C%20and%20if%20tomorrow's%20giants%20never%20need%20to%20bulk%20up%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20we%20may%20well%20be%20witnessing%20the%20end%20of%20a%20defining%20feature%20of%20corporate%20America%3A%20the%20mega-employer.%20That%20could%20give%20rise%20to%20a%20whole%20new%20generation%20of%20nimble%20companies%20that%20innovate%20faster%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20leave%20workers%20navigating%20a%20world%20of%20diminished%20career%20paths%20and%20fewer%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution%2C%20most%20Americans%20worked%20for%20themselves%20as%20farmers%20or%20craftsmen.%20And%20those%20who%20didn't%20worked%20for%20very%20small%20operations%20%E2%80%94%20say%2C%20a%20few%20journeymen%20training%20under%20a%20master%20shoemaker.%20The%20resulting%20economy%20was%20a%20patchwork%20of%20all%20these%20tiny%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20started%20to%20change%20with%20the%20advent%20of%20capital-intensive%20industries%20like%20textile%20manufacturing%2C%20which%20required%20organizing%20larger%20groups%20of%20people%20under%20a%20single%20employer.%20Then%20came%20railroads%20in%20the%20late%2019th%20century.%20With%20projects%20that%20took%20many%20years%20to%20realize%20and%20stretched%20over%20thousands%20of%20miles%2C%20vast%20numbers%20of%20workers%20needed%20to%20be%20on%20the%20same%20page.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20mess%20it%20up%2C%20there's%20a%20big%20explosion%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Louis%20Hyman%2C%20a%20historian%20of%20work%20and%20business%20at%20Cornell.%20%26quot%3BYou%20needed%20to%20really%20coordinate%20your%20mechanisms%20and%20make%20sure%20that%20people%20are%20doing%20things%20exactly%20the%20same%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20mass%20production%20developed%2C%20Hyman%20says%2C%20many%20of%20the%20most%20consequential%20innovations%20during%20this%20time%20weren't%20so%20much%20technical%20breakthroughs%3A%20They%20were%20social%20inventions%20to%20coordinate%20the%20labor%20of%20all%20the%20people%20it%20took%20to%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20the%20new%20machines.%20The%20assembly%20line%20broke%20down%20complicated%20work%20into%20simple%2C%20repeatable%2C%20standardized%20tasks%3B%20scientific%20management%20emphasized%20the%20importance%20of%20monitoring%2C%20measuring%2C%20and%20optimizing%20everyone's%20performance%3B%20and%20the%20M-form%20corporate%20structure%20created%20a%20blueprint%20to%20manage%20sprawling%20bureaucracies%20through%20a%20clear%20chain%20of%20command.%20In%20the%201930s%2C%20about%20a%20tenth%20of%20the%20labor%20force%20worked%20for%20businesses%20that%20employed%20at%20least%2010%2C000%20people.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20World%20War%20II%2C%20that%20share%20had%20surged%20to%20about%20a%20third.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%201970s%2C%20some%20of%20that%20bigger-is-better%20ideology%20started%20to%20change.%20A%20new%20management%20philosophy%20set%20in%2C%20normalizing%20layoffs%20that%20took%20aim%20at%20bloat.%20And%20as%20robots%20automated%20many%20blue-collar%20jobs%2C%20IBM%20mainframes%20and%20word%20processors%20eliminated%20a%20whole%20set%20of%20white-collar%20clerical%20roles%20as%20well.%20Still%2C%20there%20was%20plenty%20of%20work%20that%20technology%20couldn't%20automate%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20companies%20needed%20large%20teams%20of%20college-educated%20professionals%20to%20keep%20them%20going.%20Even%20the%20most%20tech-forward%20companies%20saw%20their%20people%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20their%20coders%20%E2%80%94%20as%20mission-critical%20to%20their%20success.%20%26quot%3BHiring%20great%20people%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20engineers%20%E2%80%94%20is%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20that%20any%20technology%20company%20has%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.inc.com%2Feric-markowitz%2Fcan-zuck-really-not-find-enough-engineers.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%20lamented%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202013.%20%26quot%3BOur%20country%20doesn't%20produce%20the%20volume%20of%20engineers%20that%20the%20companies%20would%20want%20to%20hire.%26quot%3B%20Tech%20giants%20often%20hired%20more%20than%20they%20needed%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20had%20a%20steady%20supply%20of%20talent%2C%20and%20to%20attract%20and%20retain%20the%20best%20of%20the%20best%2C%20they%20treated%20their%20employees%20like%20gods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20were%20to%20pinpoint%20one%20moment%20the%20gods%20turned%20mortal%2C%20it%20would%20probably%20be%20November%209%2C%202022%20%E2%80%94%20the%20day%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-employees-facebook-mark-zuckerberg-metaverse-bet-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20laid%20off%20%3C%2Fa%3Emore%20than%2011%2C000%20employees.%20From%20there%2C%20virtually%20every%20tech%20company%20followed%20suit%2C%20with%20employers%20across%20other%20industries%20close%20behind.%20At%20first%2C%20the%20cuts%20were%20chalked%20up%20to%20overhiring%20in%20the%20pandemic.%20But%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20later%2C%20the%20layoffs%20haven't%20stopped%20and%20hiring%20is%20still%20down.%20More%20and%20more%2C%20AI%20appears%20to%20be%20driving%20those%20austerity%20measures.%20In%20an%20industry%20that%20once%20hoarded%20talent%20like%20gold%2C%20the%20shift%20is%20striking.%20CEOs%20no%20longer%20seem%20to%20view%20the%20bulk%20of%20their%20workforce%20as%20indispensable%2C%20and%20they%20say%20as%20much%3A%20A%20common%20refrain%20among%20tech%20leaders%20from%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20to%20Elon%20Musk%20to%20Dara%20Khosrowshahi%20now%20is%20some%20version%20of%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20like%20it%20here%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatt-ceo-memo-workplace-loyalty-dead-employees-job-security-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyou%20should%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Companies%20like%20Microsoft%2C%20Meta%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Salesforce%20had%20reliably%20increased%20their%20headcounts%20year%20after%20year.%20Now%2C%20according%20to%20the%20workforce%20analytics%20provider%20Live%20Data%2C%20all%20of%20them%20employ%20fewer%20people%20than%20they%20did%20at%20their%202022%20peak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FhZcsb%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22big%20tech%20headcount%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22551%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EJ.%20Scott%20Hamilton%2C%20Live%20Data's%20CEO%2C%20says%20this%20is%20probably%20just%20the%20beginning.%20To%20gauge%20how%20much%20deeper%20the%20cuts%20could%20go%2C%20his%20team%20recently%20analyzed%20the%20detailed%20responsibilities%20of%20most%20roles%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ceo-memo-job-cuts-profit-enigma-of-success-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20estimate%20the%20share%20of%20tasks%20that%20could%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20be%20done%20by%20AI.%20Their%20conclusion%3A%20If%20Microsoft%20were%20to%20offload%20all%20of%20those%20automatable%20tasks%20to%20AI%2C%20it%20would%20eliminate%2036%25%20of%20the%20work%20currently%20done%20by%20employees.%20That%20would%20mean%20the%20company%20could%20lay%20off%20some%2080%2C000%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20that's%20an%20aggressive%20scenario%3A%20Companies%20are%20rarely%20able%20to%20overhaul%20their%20workflows%20to%20take%20full%20advantage%20of%20a%20new%20automation%20technology's%20capabilities.%20If%20they%20do%2C%20that%20transition%20takes%20a%20very%20long%20time.%20And%20besides%2C%20some%20work%20is%20simply%20too%20high-stakes%20to%20entrust%20to%20error-prone%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20it's%20technically%20possible.%20On%20the%20other%2C%20the%20estimate%20may%20prove%20conservative%3A%20Live%20Data's%20predictions%20assume%20that%20AI%20will%20remain%20at%202025-level%20capabilities.%20Given%20how%20much%20better%20the%20leading%20large%20language%20models%20have%20become%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20the%20best%20tools%20will%20almost%20certainly%20be%20able%20to%20handle%20more%20than%20what%20they%20can%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20optimists%20are%20saying%20that%20the%20good%20companies%20will%20simply%20redeploy%20the%20assets%20elsewhere%20now%20that%20they%20can%20be%20more%20efficient%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamilton%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20think%20an%20equal%20argument%20can%20be%20made%20that%20they'll%20just%20say%2C%20'We're%20going%20to%20do%20the%20same%20amount%20with%20fewer%20people.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20sounds%20like%20a%20far-off%20hypothetical%20future%2C%20consider%20what's%20already%20happening%20today%20at%20startups.%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20says%20he's%20making%20bets%20with%20his%20friends%20on%20when%20we'll%20get%20the%20first%20%26quot%3Bone-person%20billion-dollar%20company.%26quot%3B%20And%20Arthur%20Kaneko%2C%20a%20general%20partner%20at%20Coreline%20Ventures%2C%20tells%20me%20he's%20noticed%20that%20early-stage%20founders%20are%20raising%20their%20initial%20rounds%20of%20funding%20with%20fewer%20employees%20than%20they%20would%20have%20had%20in%20the%20past%20%E2%80%94%20among%20the%20AI-fluent%20founders%2C%20perhaps%20with%20less%20than%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20way%20companies%20are%20being%20built%20is%20just%20fundamentally%20changing%20right%20now%20because%20of%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20Kaneko%20says.%20%26quot%3BThrough%20the%20use%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-ai-technology-end-of-coding-software-developers-jobs-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20coding%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20AI%20marketing%2C%20AI%20sales%2C%20people%20are%20able%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20more%20work%20with%20way%20fewer%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20he%20thinks%20these%20startups%20will%20stay%20lean%20as%20they%20scale%20into%20successful%20businesses.%20%26quot%3BThey%20just%20won't%20hire%20the%20people%20that%20Meta%20and%20Microsoft%20had%20to%20hire%20to%20get%20to%20where%20they%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20per-company%20headcount%20will%20permanently%20be%20depressed%20in%20startups.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20reasons%20to%20be%20hopeful%20about%20a%20new%20era%20of%20smaller%20employers.%20If%20AI%20makes%20it%20cheaper%20and%20easier%20to%20launch%20companies%2C%20we'll%20probably%20see%20more%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20would%20be%20great%20for%20the%20long-term%20health%20of%20the%20economy%20in%20all%20kinds%20of%20ways.%20New%20businesses%20tend%20to%20employ%20people%20with%20less%20experience%20and%20fewer%20credentials%20who%20get%20passed%20up%20by%20the%20bigger%20companies.%20They're%20more%20willing%20to%20try%20new%20things%2C%20which%20drives%20innovation.%20And%20they%20create%20more%20competition%20for%20the%20established%20giants%2C%20which%20is%20good%20for%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmaller%20companies%20may%20also%20be%20good%20for%20the%20workers%20inside%20them.%20There's%20a%20lot%20that%20people%20hate%20about%20working%20at%20big%20organizations%3A%20the%20constant%20turf%20wars%2C%20the%20endless%20layers%20of%20approval%2C%20the%20meetings%20before%20the%20meetings%2C%20the%20sense%20that%20you're%20just%20one%20tiny%20inconsequential%20cog%20in%20a%20giant%20machine.%20Smaller%20bureaucracies%20would%20minimize%20that%2C%20which%20is%20one%20reason%20why%20people%20often%20feel%20more%20motivated%20in%20leaner%20workplaces.%20According%20to%20Gallup%2C%20employees%20at%20small%20companies%20report%20the%20highest%20engagement%2C%20with%20scores%20dropping%20below%20the%20national%20average%20once%20organizations%20hit%20500%20employees.%20On%20the%20same%20stage%20where%20Altman%20made%20his%20one-person%20unicorn%20prediction%2C%20Reddit%20co-founder%20Alexis%20Ohanian%20raved%20about%20the%20benefits%20of%20this%20possibility.%20%26quot%3BCEOs%20and%20founders%20are%20going%20to%20be%20so%20excited%20to%20get%20up%20and%20go%20to%20work%20with%20much%20smaller%2C%20much%20more%20performant%2C%20much%20more%20culturally%20strong%20teams%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20world%20of%20shrunken%20employers%20could%20also%20rob%20workers%20of%20something%20essential%3A%20the%20long-term%20career%20paths%20that%20big%20companies%20used%20to%20offer.%20With%20so%20many%20roles%20under%20one%20roof%2C%20big%20companies%20made%20it%20possible%20for%20workers%20to%20try%20new%20things%2C%20move%20up%2C%20and%20build%20careers.%20Smaller%20firms%20don't%20offer%20the%20same%20range%20of%20opportunities%2C%20which%20means%20people%20will%20likely%20need%20to%20switch%20companies%20a%20lot%20more%20in%20the%20future.%20Smaller%20firms%20are%20also%20less%20likely%20to%20invest%20in%20on-the-job%20training%20%E2%80%94%20a%20shift%20that%20would%20hit%20early-career%20professionals%20hard%2C%20just%20as%20their%20roles%20face%20the%20greatest%20risk%20from%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20question%20is%20what%20this%20all%20means%20for%20college-educated%20workers.%20If%20enough%20startups%20emerge%2C%20they%20might%20create%20new%20jobs%20to%20offset%20the%20ones%20disappearing%20from%20big%20companies.%20But%20that%20would%20require%20an%20unprecedented%20boom%20in%20entrepreneurship%20%E2%80%94%20one%20enormous%20enough%20to%20make%20up%20for%20the%20retrenchment%20of%20the%20giants.%20In%202022%2C%2029%25%20of%20the%20American%20workforce%20worked%20for%20an%20organization%20that%20employed%20at%20least%2010%2C000%20people.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20country's%20education%20system%20is%20churning%20out%20ever%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-damage-gen-z-careers-tech-layoffs-job-market-hiring-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20grads%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20studied%20hard%20with%20the%20expectation%20of%20a%20stable%20future%20in%20white-collar%20work.%20If%20big%20companies%20hire%20less%2C%20and%20small%20companies%20also%20hire%20less%2C%20where%20will%20they%20all%20go%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20usual%20reassurance%20is%20that%20AI%2C%20like%20every%20disruptive%20technology%20before%20it%2C%20will%20eventually%20create%20more%20jobs%20than%20it%20destroys.%20That%20glosses%20over%20an%20important%20detail%2C%20according%20to%20Carl%20Benedikt%20Frey%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Oxford.%20In%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution%2C%20most%20innovations%20simply%20made%20existing%20work%20faster%20and%20cheaper%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20loom%2C%20which%20automated%20the%20work%20of%20skilled%20weavers%20but%20still%20produced%20more%20or%20less%20the%20same%20fabric.%20That%20made%20a%20handful%20of%20industrialists%20very%20rich%2C%20but%20for%20the%20average%20worker%2C%20wages%20barely%20budged%20for%20the%20first%2080%20or%20so%20years%20of%20industrialization.%20It%20was%20only%20later%20%E2%80%94%20with%20inventions%20like%20electricity%20and%20the%20automobile%20that%20gave%20rise%20to%20entirely%20novel%20industries%20%E2%80%94%20that%20economic%20growth%20surged%20and%20better%2C%20high-paying%20jobs%20emerged.%20Had%20that%20second%20wave%20never%20arrived%2C%20we'd%20remember%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution%20very%20differently.%20%26quot%3BMost%20productivity%20gains%20over%20the%20long%20run%2C%26quot%3B%20Frey%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bcome%20from%20doing%20new%20and%20previously%20inconceivable%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20corporate%20America%20seems%20stuck%20in%20that%20first%20phase.%20So%20many%20executives%20are%20laser-focused%20on%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatgpt-replace-jobs-unemployment-salaries-technology-economist-daron-acemoglu-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20to%20do%20the%20same%20work%20with%20fewer%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rather%20than%20applying%20it%20to%20problems%20we%20couldn't%20solve%20before%20%E2%80%94%20the%20kind%20of%20breakthroughs%20that%20would%20open%20up%20new%20lines%20of%20business%20and%20generate%20more%20demand%20for%20labor%2C%20not%20less.%20%26quot%3BA%20real%20risk%20is%20that%20we're%20getting%20leaner%20organizations%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20really%20creating%20that%20much%20new%2C%26quot%3B%20Frey%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat%20would%20be%20a%20bleak%20future%2C%20and%20I%20do%20worry%20we're%20moving%20in%20that%20direction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-biggest-employers-facing-great-shrinking-corporations-ai-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754899741000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68950e48f748d8c055f71d19%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-biggest-employers-facing-great-shrinking-corporations-ai-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20more%20than%20a%20century%2C%20armies%20of%20office%20workers%20were%20a%20necessary%20cost%20of%20doing%20business%20in%20corporate%20America.%20Not%20anymore..%20Not%20anymore.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aito%40businessinsider.com%20(Aki%20Ito)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A69%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-biggest-employers-facing-great-shrinking-corporations-ai-2025-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Mahavatar%20Narsimha%E2%80%9