ucceed%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Greg%20Brockman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689964dd194a2d49b8ae50cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI's%20cofounder%2C%20Greg%20Brockman%2C%20says%20engineers%20need%20%26quot%3Btechnical%20humility%26quot%3B%20to%20succeed%20at%20the%20company.%3Cp%3EErrich%20Petersen%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20SXSW%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI's%20cofounder%20says%20engineers%20joining%20his%20company%20need%20to%20check%20their%20ego%20at%20the%20door.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BTechnical%20humility%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20critical%20quality%20for%20engineers%20to%20succeed%20at%20OpenAI%2C%20Greg%20Brockman%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKnowing%20when%20to%20trust%20your%20instincts%20and%20when%20to%20leave%20them%20behind%20is%20key%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20cofounder%20and%20president%2C%20Greg%20Brockman%2C%20has%20one%20piece%20of%20advice%20for%20engineers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-competition-big-tech-meta-talent-windsurf-amazon-movie-deepmind-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejoining%20his%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Check%20your%20ego%20at%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20critical%20quality%20for%20engineers%20to%20succeed%20at%20OpenAI%20is%20%26quot%3Btechnical%20humility%2C%20Brockman%20said%20at%20the%20AI%20Engineer%20World's%20Fair%20in%20San%20Francisco%20on%20June%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20coming%20in%20because%20you%20have%20skills%20that%20are%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20video%20recording%20of%20the%20session%20that%20was%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epublished%20on%20AI%20Engineer's%20YouTube%20channel%20on%20Monday.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20a%20totally%20different%20environment%20from%20something%20like%20a%20traditional%20web%20startup.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20insight%2C%20he%20said%2C%20came%20from%20watching%20culture%20clashes%20between%20colleagues%20from%20engineering%20and%20research%20backgrounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20engineers%20often%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BWe've%20agreed%20on%20an%20interface%2C%20I%20can%20implement%20it%20however%20I%20want.%26quot%3B%20Researchers%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20see%20the%20system%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20where%20even%20a%20tiny%20bug%20can%20quietly%20degrade%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20early%20project%2C%20Brockman%20said%20OpenAI's%20engineering%20team%20ground%20to%20a%20halt%20debating%20every%20line%20of%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20solution%20was%20simple.%20He'd%20propose%20five%20ideas%2C%20a%20researcher%20would%20reject%20four%2C%20and%20they'd%20move%20forward%20with%20the%20one%20that%20remained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20for%20engineers%2C%20Brockman%20said%2C%20is%20knowing%20when%20to%20trust%20your%20instincts%20and%20when%20to%20leave%20them%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20to%20come%20in%2C%20really%20listen%2C%20and%20kind%20of%20assume%20that%20there's%20something%20that%20you're%20missing%20until%20you%20deeply%20understand%20the%20why%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThen%2C%20at%20that%20point%2C%20great%2C%20make%20the%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrockman%20and%20OpenAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f0389f87-7664-485f-9dcb-c3b2a8fe0d42%5C%22%3EWhat%20it%20takes%20to%20succeed%20at%20OpenAI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELeaders%20at%20OpenAI%20have%20spoken%20about%20what%20it%20takes%20for%20employees%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chatgpt-employee-job-advice-nick-turley-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethrive%20at%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BApproaching%20each%20scenario%20from%20scratch%20is%20so%20important%20in%20this%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20Nick%20Turley%2C%20the%20head%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Lenny%20Rachitsky%20on%20his%20weekly%20tech%20podcast%20on%20Saturday.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20analogy%20for%20what%20we're%20building.%20You%20can't%20copy%20an%20existing%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20OpenAI%20cannot%20iterate%20on%20products%20or%20features%20developed%20by%20tech%20giants%20like%20Instagram%20or%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20learn%20from%20everywhere%2C%20but%20you%20have%20to%20do%20it%20from%20scratch.%20That's%20why%20that%20trait%20tends%20to%20make%20someone%20effective%20at%20OpenAI%2C%20and%20it's%20something%20we%20test%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20an%20employee's%20ability%20to%20start%20a%20project%20from%20the%20ground%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20OpenAI's%20interview%20guide%2C%20which%20is%20published%20on%20its%20website%2C%20the%20company%20looks%20for%20candidates%20who%20can%20%26quot%3Bramp%20up%20quickly%20in%20a%20new%20domain%20and%20produce%20results.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20values%20%26quot%3Bcollaboration%2C%20effective%20communication%2C%20openness%20to%20feedback%2C%20and%20alignment%20with%20our%20mission%E2%81%A0%20and%20values%E2%81%A0.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrockman%2C%20a%20software%20engineer%20by%20training%2C%20dropped%20out%20of%20MIT%20to%20join%20the%20payments%20startup%20Stripe%20in%202010%2C%20becoming%20its%20CTO%20before%20leaving%20in%202015%20to%20cofound%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20took%20a%20three-month%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-president-greg-brockman-quits-sam-altman-ceo-ousted-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleave%20of%20absence%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20company%20in%20